      <section eId="sec_82_87_060">
        <num>RCW 82.87.060</num>
        <heading>Deductions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_87_060__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A standard deduction of $250,000 per individual, or in the case of spouses or domestic partners, their combined standard deduction is limited to $250,000, regardless of whether they file joint or separate returns. The amount of the standard deduction shall be adjusted pursuant to RCW
82.87.150
;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_87_060__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Amounts that the state is prohibited from taxing under the Constitution of this state or the Constitution or laws of the United States;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_87_060__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The amount of adjusted capital gain derived from the sale or transfer of the taxpayer's interest in a qualified family-owned small business pursuant to RCW
82.87.070
; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_87_060__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
